  "notes": "Jiji cabinet approval fell below 50% (<b>49.0%</b>) in July 2026 for the first time since PM Takaichi took office in Oct 2025 — a fourth straight monthly decline, with disapproval up to 25.2%. The LDP–JIP (Ishin) coalition's push to force through key bills (including a secondary-capital law) plus the cost-of-living and energy squeeze are eroding support. <b>Market read:</b> a weakening cabinet raises the odds of additional fiscal stimulus / slower consolidation (JGB-supply negative) and gives the government more incentive to lean against a weak yen — a backdrop that keeps pressure on the BOJ's normalisation path. Other pollsters run higher or lower by level (JNN/Yomiuri highest, Mainichi lowest — Mainichi's July reading was 41%), but all show the same downtrend; Jiji is used here as a single consistent monthly series.",
